    <description>The Automatic Concept Extraction project's goal is to reduce the amount of time a user spends filtering through
    search engine result links to find the desired result. ACE is a graphical user interface written in java that acts as a front-end
    to a search engine (or set of search engines). ACE forwards a user's query to the search engine(s), then displays an integrated set of result
    links. Then, rather than having the user manual filter through the results by visiting each page in the result set, ACE can be told to automatically
    extract a "concept map", that describes the actual content of the page. The concept map is generated by pluggable, Scorer, components. Developers can
    plug in their own scoring algorithms using ACE's extensible architecture. Given a concept map, the user need not visit pages which don't have the 
    desirable concepts that the user was searching for.
    </description>
    
